      • pushState

        H pushState(java.lang.Object obj,
            java.lang.String title,
            java.lang.String url)
        Pushes the object onto the browser history with a name and url hash to put in the URL bar
        Parameters:
        obj - Any object that contains any state we want to remember for a history element (usually a history closure object with a view that can be displayed)
        title - Title of the History Element to be saved (not used)
        url - URL hash to display in the URL bar indicating which history element is being displayed
        Returns:
        Returns the history object so additional methods could be called on it
